# SBIG CCDOPS - CCD astronomical camera image format (Type 3)
# Created by Santa Barbara Instrument Group (SBIG), est. 1988.
# 2048-byte ASCII header with camera model, exposure, dimensions etc.
# followed by 14-bit or 16-bit little-endian pixel data.
# Spec: formerly at sbig.com (now diffractionlimited.com)
# Netpbm: sbigtopgm, pgmtosbig

# Header line 1 is always "ST-N Image" or "ST-NN Image"
# where N is the camera model number (4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 237, 402, etc.)
# Note: LF-CR line endings per spec (yes, really)

0	string	ST-
>&0	regex	[0-9]+\ Image	SBIG CCDOPS CCD camera image
!:mime	image/x-sbig
!:ext	sbig
